                            <comment id="15120210" author="dragonsinth" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2016 21:38:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Introduced i &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7220&quot; title=&quot;comments for query strings&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7220&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7220&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regular expression queries that start with an escaped forward-slash don&apos;t work anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Works: foo:/ab\/c/
Does not work: foo:/\/abc/
Work around, put the beginning slash in a character class: foo:/[\/]abc/
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached a patch to fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
